At an event, which was popular a lot on Thai social networks, there was a student who sprayed paint his wall and painted some words, including ‘PM, are you going to restore Monarchy?” This couldn’t make people calm down, especially the Palace, which led to many assemblyman gathering and holding a demonstration at Parliament. Concluding the process of restoring Thai democracy, Thaksin Shinawatra was removed from the Prime Minister’s post. He had to escape to abroad after facing extradition issues.

The next PM, Samak Sundaravej had a continuing trial, which involved the seizure of power. PM had to allocate the best solutions and an effective trial of his minister: KRungthep Thurakit publicly announced Thaksin Shinawatra guilty of wrongdoing.
